<div id="review_2163646720" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2163646720" />
    <a title="Moushine Zahr" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/53509133-moushine-zahr"><img alt="Moushine Zahr" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1457457507p2/53509133.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2163646720?book_show_action=true">Oct 30, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Moushine Zahr" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Moushine Zahr" href="/user/show/53509133-moushine-zahr">Moushine Zahr</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback 9782253062066" href="/book/show/3295.Les_Contes_d_Eva_Luna">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2163646720" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer47526743726892878">This novel contains a number of fiction short stories, in which all the central character are mostly women, all set in Chili, and set during the late 19th centure and first half of 20th century. Some stories are interesting while others not. I was neither attracted to one specific story nor disliked another in particular. Like most short stories novel, I don&apos;t have much to say about them. </span>
  <span id="freeText47526743726892878" style="display:none">This novel contains a number of fiction short stories, in which all the central character are mostly women, all set in Chili, and set during the late 19th centure and first half of 20th century. Some stories are interesting while others not. I was neither attracted to one specific story nor disliked another in particular. Like most short stories novel, I don't have much to say about them. </span>
  <a data-text-id="47526743726892878" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


